  <Text>k__BackingField: The capitalists knew that this was considered unpaid labour,
    so they wanted more women to join the workforce to contribute to the economy,
    which obviously means they earn more money. At the same time, having women working
    meant they can have their own income to spend more on goods and services, thereby
    adding more people to the customer base.
